cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. The paper proposes a dual network to better utilize features among layers for visual tracking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the training of the network, which involves measuring the similarities between the network activation and target appearance, which is related to machine learning and deep learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses the use of prior maps to enhance performance, which is related to artificial intelligence and computer graphics, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. The paper also evaluates the proposed algorithm on two large-scale benchmark datasets, which is related to multimedia and robotics, making cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.RO (Robotics) possible categories as well.
